{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:34:52.279386+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The `Limiter.check()` method implements a **token-bucket rate limiter** using a Redis Lua script for atomicity. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\n## **Inputs**\n- **`key`** (`str`): Arbitrary identifier for the entity being rate-limited (e.g., user ID, IP address).\n- **`cost`** (`int`, default `1`): Number of tokens to consume per request.\n\n## **Initialization** (constructor)\n- Connects to Redis via `redis_url`.\n- Stores `capacity` (maximum tokens) and `refill_per_sec` (refill rate).\n- Loads the Lua script (`bucket.lua`) into Redis via `SCRIPT LOAD`, saving the SHA.\n\n## **Step-by-Step Execution of `check()`**\n\n### 1. **Key Formatting**\n```python\nbucket_key = f\"rl:{{{key}}}\"\n```\n- Prefixes with `rl:` and wraps `{key}` in curly braces for Redis Cluster hash-tag compatibility, ensuring the same key always routes to the same node.\n\n### 2. **Execute Lua Script Atomically**\n```python\nresult = self._r.evalsha(self._sha, 1, bucket_key, str(self._capacity), str(self._refill), str(cost))\n```\n- Calls the pre-loaded script via `EVALSHA` with:\n  - `KEYS[1]` = `bucket_key`\n  - `ARGV[1]` = capacity (string)\n  - `ARGV[2]` = refill rate (string)\n  - `ARGV[3]` = cost (string)\n\n### 3. **Inside the Lua Script (Redis‑side)**\n\n#### a. **Get Server Time**\n```lua\nlocal now_ms = redis.call(\"TIME\")\nnow_ms = now_ms[1] * 1000 + math.floor(now_ms[2] / 1000)\n```\nConverts Redis server time to milliseconds.\n\n#### b. **Load Bucket State**\n```lua\nlocal state = redis.call(\"HMGET\", key, \"tokens\", \"ts\")\nlocal tokens = tonumber(state[1])\nlocal last_ts = tonumber(state[2])\n```\nReads two fields from a Redis hash at the key:\n- `tokens`: current token level (float stored as string)\n- `ts`: last‑update timestamp (ms)\n\nIf missing, initializes a **new bucket**:\n```lua\nif tokens == nil or last_ts == nil then\n    tokens = capacity\n    last_ts = now_ms\nend\n```\nNew bucket starts **full** at capacity.\n\n#### c. **Refill Tokens**\n```lua\nlocal elapsed_sec = math.max(0, (now_ms - last_ts) / 1000.0)\ntokens = math.min(capacity, tokens + elapsed_sec * refill)\n```\n- Calculates seconds since last update.\n- Adds `elapsed_sec * refill` tokens, capped at capacity.\n\n#### d. **Consume Tokens**\n```lua\nlocal allowed = 0\nif tokens >= cost then\n    tokens = tokens - cost\n    allowed = 1\nend\n```\n- If enough tokens, subtracts `cost` and sets `allowed = 1`.\n- Otherwise, `allowed` stays `0`.\n\n#### e. **Persist State**\n```lua\nredis.call(\"HMSET\", key, \"tokens\", tostring(tokens), \"ts\", tostring(now_ms))\n```\nWrites back the new token count and current timestamp.\n\n#### f. **Set TTL**\n```lua\nlocal ttl = math.max(60, math.ceil(capacity / refill * 10))\nredis.call(\"EXPIRE\", key, ttl)\n```\n- Auto‑deletes inactive buckets after 10× the full‑refill time (minimum 60 seconds).\n\n#### g. **Return**\n```lua\nreturn {allowed, math.floor(tokens)}\n```\nReturns allowed (0/1) and remaining tokens (floored integer).\n\n### 4. **Python Side Interpretation**\n```python\nallowed = bool(result[0])\nremaining = int(result[1])\nreturn allowed, remaining\n```\nConverts allowed to boolean and remaining to integer.\n\n## **Return Value**\n- **`Tuple[bool, int]`**:\n  - `allowed`: `True` if request permitted, `False` otherwise.\n  - `remaining`: Integer tokens left (non‑negative, because consumption only happens if enough tokens).\n\n## **Side Effects on Redis**\n1. **Creates/updates a Redis hash** at key `rl:{key}` with fields:\n   - `tokens`: updated token count (string representing float).\n   - `ts`: current timestamp in milliseconds.\n2. **Sets TTL** via `EXPIRE` so unused buckets are automatically deleted.\n3. **No other side effects**: the Lua script is atomic—no intermediate state is visible to other clients.\n\n## **Key Design Points**\n- **Atomicity**: the entire refill‑and‑consume sequence runs as a single Redis command (`EVALSHA`), eliminating race conditions.\n- **Token‑bucket algorithm**: classic implementation with constant refill rate up to a maximum capacity.\n- **Cluster‑compatible**: hash tags `{key}` ensure operations on the same logical key go to the same Redis Cluster node.\n- **Persistence**: bucket state survives application restarts (until TTL expires).\n\nThis design guarantees accurate rate limiting even under high concurrency, because the Lua script executes atomically within Redis.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 2387, "prompt_tokens": 6335, "total_tokens": 8722, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 1256, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5888, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0022923318, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002156418, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00207669}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864451-nLSsQquyYCi0Mz7njqXE", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3cb-0279-7960-8eb9-79c8540fe7e4-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6335, "output_tokens": 2387, "total_tokens": 8722, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5888}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1256}}}}]}}}
